javax.jaxtx.acid
Interface ACIDTransaction

public interface ACIDTransaction

Instances of this interface represent specific ACID transactions. This interface allows participants to be enlisted with the transaction. Unlike when terminating a transaction through the UserACIDTransaction or ACIDTransactionManager interfaces, terminating the transaction via this interface does not change the thread-to-transaction association.

commit

public void commit()
            throws InvalidTransactionException,
                   WrongStateException,
                   HeuristicHazardException,
                   HeuristicMixedException,
                   SystemException,
                   TransactionRolledBackException
Commit the transaction. All participants that are still enlisted with the transaction are committed.

Throws:
InvalidTransactionException - Thrown if the current transaction is not known about by the transaction system.
WrongStateException - Thrown if the current transaction is not in a state that allows commit to be called.
HeuristicHazardException - Thrown if the participants generated a hazard heuristic.
HeuristicMixedException - Thrown if the participants generated a mixed heuristic.
SystemException - Thrown if some other error occurred.
TransactionRolledBackException

Abort the transaction. All participants that are still enlisted with the transaction are rolled back.

Throws:

HeuristicHazardException - Thrown if the participants generated a hazard heuristic.
HeuristicMixedException - Thrown if the participants generated a mixed heuristic.
SystemException - Thrown if some other error occurred.

setRollbackOnly

public void setRollbackOnly()
                     throws WrongStateException,
                            SystemException
Set the state of the transaction such that the only possible outcome is for it to rollback.

Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the state of the transaction is such that it is not possible to put it into a rollback-only state, e.g., it is committing.
SystemException - Thrown if any other error occurs.

enlistParticipant

public RecoveryCoordinator enlistParticipant(TwoPhaseParticipant participant)
                                      throws WrongStateException,
                                             InvalidTransactionException,
                                             SystemException
Enrol the specified participant in the current transaction such that it will be invoked during the two-phase commit protocol. If successful, a RecoveryCoordinator will be returned to the participant, which should be recorded durability such that it may be used later in the event of failure.

Returns:
the RecoveryCoordinator instance that is bound to this participant and may be used to instigate failure recovery processes.
Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the transaction is not in a state whereby participants can be enrolled.
InvalidTransactionException - Thrown if the transaction associated with the thread is invalid.
SystemException - Thrown if any other error occurs.
See Also:
RecoveryCoordinator

enlistSynchronization

public void enlistSynchronization(Synchronization participant)
                           throws WrongStateException,
                                  InvalidTransactionException,
                                  SystemException
Enlist a synchronization with the current transaction. Synchronizations do not receive the two-phase commit messages but instead are invoked prior to its start and after it has completed.

Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the transaction state is such that synchronizations cannot be enrolled.
InvalidTransactionException - Thrown if the transaction is not top-level.
SystemException - Thrown if any other error occurs.
